	<h2 style="margin-bottom:0px;">High I Performance Management</h2>
	<h1 style="text-align:center; margin-top:0px;">Strengths and Weaknesses</h1>
	<br>
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Planning and Goal Setting</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table1">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Creates a compelling vision</li>
					<li>Uses metaphors, models, strong verbal images to clarify</li>
					<li>Sees the big picture</li>
					<li>Exhibits creative and innovative thinking </li>
					<li>Expresses energy and enthusiasm</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May not supply enough details about the how</li>
					<li>May underestimate problems and overestimate rewards</li>
					<li>Tends to generalize</li>
					<li>May over-communicate and not allow employee input</li>
					<li>May oversimplify</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Measuring and Monitoring Progress/Coaching</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Encourages participation and discussion</li>
					<li>Applauds successes</li>
					<li>Encourages more than demands</li>
					<li>Discerns what’s important to employee</li>
					<li>Strives for consensus and good will</li>
					<li>Provides lots of communication opportunities</li>
					<li>Friendly and approachable</li>
					<li>Takes time with people</li>
					<li>Builds rapport with employees</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Deals in generalities, promises</li>
					<li>May exaggerate both progress and shortfalls</li>
					<li>May not prepare adequate for coaching sessions</li>
					<li>May jump to conclusions without listening to feedback</li>
					<li>May soften suggestions in order to be liked</li>
					<li>May skirt tough issue to maintain good will</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Evaluating Performance</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table3">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May solicit opinions of others for a balanced view </li>
					<li>Able to articulate clearly</li>
					<li>Develops suggestions about next steps</li>
					<li>Sees performance appraisal as mutually beneficial and not judgmental</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May prepare inadequately</li>
					<li>May suffer from “halo” effect:  compatibility, past performance, one outstanding strength</li>
					<li>Insufficient follow-through</li>
					<li>May get into character analysis in cases of poor performance</li>
					<li>May focus on most recent events</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Conducting Development Review Session/Strategies</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table4">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Celebrates accomplishments</li>
					<li>Creates non-threatening environment</li>
					<li>Encourages participation and response</li>
					<li>Let’s people know what’s next</li>
					<li>Links individual’s needs to organization’s needs</li>
					<li>Wants employee to be in best environment for that person</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May be overly optimistic</li>
					<li>Tends to go off on tangents</li>
					<li>May turn session into social call</li>
					<li>May over-communicate and talk too much</li>
					<li>May give vague instructions</li>
					<li>Dislikes confronting or giving negative feedback; may downplay</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>